cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a domain-specific language for encoding induction heuristics in Isabelle/HOL, a proof assistant based on higher-order logic. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper presents a tool for transferring expertise in Isabelle/HOL to new users, which can be seen as a software engineering problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new language, LiFtEr, for encoding induction heuristics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses a tool for automating inductive theorem proving, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper presents a systematic way of transferring expertise, which is a common problem in machine learning.
